main event: Three unidentified objects were observed in Huntsville, Alabama, on May 9, 1964, for a duration of 8-10 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were tracked using ground radar, measurements estimated their speed to be about 35 mph, the objects were thought to be landing lights but appeared to be in conflict with the stated condition of lighting, the objects were moving north during the observation, further analysis was requested by the Air Force regarding changes in the objects' light.
witness description: The witness was a 14-year-old male who reported the sighting.
